items.title: Trump admin live updates: Trump fires Librarian of Congress Carla Hayden
items.description: Librarian of Congress Carla Hayden was notified of her termination by an email from the White House Office of Personnel Management.

items.title: Chicago reacts to the election of the city's own Pope Leo XIV
items.description: When news broke Thursday about Robert Prevost's election as the first American pontiff, Pope Leo XIV, the mood throughout Chicago was joyous.

items.title: Jewish jeweler hospitalized after axe attack in Tunisia
items.description: The Jewish owner of a jewelry store in Tunisia was hospitalized Thursday after an axe attack on the island where Africa’s oldest synagogue is located

items.title: Trump appoints Fox News host Jeanine Pirro as top prosecutor in DC
items.description: President Donald Trump said he is appointing Fox News host and ex-prosecutor Jeanine Pirro as interim U.S. attorney for the District of Columbia.
